eu.ebdit.duckapter.annotation
Annotation Type Property

@Documented
@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=METHOD)
public @interface Property

Declares that method is property getter/setter. Annotated methods should use JavaBeans naming conventions with get*, set* and is*. Setter methods must return void and have one parameter. Getter methods must return property value and have no parameters. If there is no method of appropriate name Duckapter will try to find field with name derived from getter or setter method name. If this field is final it will not satisfy annotated setter method. Alias can contain aslo bare field name without get*, set* or is* prefix.

Author:
Vladimir Orany
